President Trump held a ceremony at the White House to honor 11 American heroes who responded to acts of violence in El Paso, Texas, and Dayton, Ohio. He awarded six police officers from Dayton with the Medal of Valor, the highest public safety award, for their swift response to the gunman and saving countless lives. Additionally, he recognized five civilians from El Paso with Certificates of Commendation for their bravery in helping others during the attack at a Walmart store. The President commended their courage, professionalism, and selflessness, and expressed gratitude to their families.